The gas turbine controls segment is anticipated to witness the highest growth due to the rising demand for gas-fired power plants and the increasing adoption of industrial gas turbines.

What are the major challenges faced by the turbomachinery controls market?
Some of the major challenges include the high initial costs of advanced control systems and the complexity of integrating control systems with existing infrastructure.

Which region is expected to dominate the turbomachinery controls market?
North America is expected to dominate the market, owing to the presence of a large number of industrial facilities and the increasing focus on automation and efficiency.

